### Chapter 19 - High-Yield Bonds (References)

- Data provided by **Professor Ed Altman**, NYU Stern School of Business
  - Key contributor of default rate calculations and junk bond performance data

### Methodological Note: Default Rate Calculations

- **Different calculation methods produce different default rates**
  - **Professor Altman (NYU)**: Compares value of defaulted bonds to **par value** of junk bonds outstanding
  - **Moody's**: Compares value of defaulted bonds to **market price** (principal value) of junk bonds outstanding
  - **Moody's includes emerging market debt** in calculations; Altman does not
  - Result: Published default rates for the same period can vary significantly depending on methodology

> "The two methods for calculating default rates result in different ratios. As a result, for any period you may see different ratios published for default rates of junk bonds."

